{
  "text": "Logistic regression is a classical method to model category data for classi\u00afcation. [CITATION_1] Suppose there are n samples with c classes and I attributes. The parameter matrix B is calculated as an I \u00c2 \u00f0c \u00c0 1\u00de matrix. The probability that the ith sample, given the value of x \u00c3 i , in the jth class but not in the last cth class is shown in Eq. (9).",
